6 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
7 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
8 Article – Courts and Judicial Proceedings
9 5–117.
10 (a) In this section, “sexual abuse” means any act that involves:
11 (1) An adult allowing or encouraging a child to engage in:
12 (i) Obscene photography, films, poses, or similar activity;
13 (ii) Pornographic photography, films, poses, or similar activity; or
14 (iii) Prostitution;
15 (2) Incest;
16 (3) Rape;
17 (4) Sexual offense in any degree; or
18 (5) Any other sexual conduct that is a crime.
19 (b) Except as provided under subsection (d) of this section and notwithstanding
20 any time limitation under a statute of limitations, a statute of repose, the Maryland Tort
21 Claims Act, the Local Government Tort Claims Act, or any other law, an action for damages
22 arising out of an alleged incident or incidents A CLAIM OR CLAIMS of sexual abuse that
23 occurred while the victim was a minor may be filed at any time.
24 (c) Except as provided in §§ 5–303 and 5–518 of this title and § 12–104 of the
25 State Government Article, the total amount of noneconomic damages that may be awarded
26 under this section to a single claimant in an action against a single defendant for injuries
27 arising from an incident or occurrence A CLAIM OR CLAIMS that would have been barred
28 by a time limitation before October 1, 2023, may not exceed:
29 (1) FOR AN ACTION FILED ON OR BEFORE MAY 31, 2025, $1,500,000;
30 AND

